message.content: Based on the process list extracted from the memory image, the most likely process responsible for the initial exploit could be AcroRd32.exe (Adobe Acrobat Reader) as it was the process associated with opening the PDF file. AcroRd32.exe is a common target for PDF-based exploits. Further analysis of this process, its memory space, and any associated network connections or file modifications would be crucial in determining the exact nature of the exploit and its impact on the system.
